io.netty.util.collection

Interface ByteObjectMap<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the value type stored in the map.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Map<Byte,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteObjectHashMap

    public interface ByteObjectMap<V>
extends Map<Byte,V>
    Interface for a primitive map that uses bytes as keys.

      • entries

        Iterable<ByteObjectMap.PrimitiveEntry<V>> entries()
        Gets an iterable to traverse over the primitive entries contained in this map. As an optimization, the ByteObjectMap.PrimitiveEntrys returned by the Iterator may change as the Iterator progresses. The caller should not rely on ByteObjectMap.PrimitiveEntry key/value stability.
